fr.loria.synalp.emotionml.descriptors
Class EmotionDescriptor

java.lang.Object
  fr.loria.synalp.emotionml.descriptors.EmotionDescriptor
Direct Known Subclasses:
ActionTendency, Appraisal, Category, Dimension
public class EmotionDescriptor
extends Object

An EmotionDescriptor is an aspect an Emotion (Category, Dimension, Appraisal or ActionTendency). All descriptors have a mandatory name and an optional value or trace. The specific constraints on the presence of value and trace depend on the type of descriptor. For instance a Dimension needs to have either a value or a trace, while a Category may lack both. All descriptors cannot have both a trace and a value. These constraints and other EmotionML constraints (see Representation of Emotions in EmotionML) are not checked when creating or modifying the descriptor, but only checked when exporting the emotion they are describing. A descriptor may be directly associated to a vocabulary URI which is a convenient way to automatically setup the Emotion vocabulary URI when attaching the descriptor to the Emotion. However, altering the URI after the descriptor has been added to the Emotion will have no effect.

Alexandre Denis
